face, and the two look at each other with cheerful, mischievous expressions.\n\nPopeye and his companions appear on the same pink ground against the soft sky. Olive Oyl, thin and long-necked, stands at the left in a red top and dark skirt. Popeye, short and muscular, wears his sailor cap, black sailor shirt, blue pants, and pipe, flexing his oversized forearms. Beside him stands a much larger bearded sailor in a yellow shirt with blue sleeves, grinning broadly. The three bounce and pose together as if bracing for rough seas or a challenge.\n\nThe Peanuts characters follow. Charlie Brown, in his yellow zigzag shirt, holds a tennis racket and a small handheld game tray; Snoopy, the white beagle, stands between Charlie Brown and Lucy. Lucy, in a blue dress, also holds a tennis racket. A tennis ball hovers near Charlie Brown’s face, and Snoopy, wearing a small visor or cap, stands alert between them, as if involved in the tennis game. The animated section fades through a warm red-and-white blur.\n\nThe commercial then moves into a live-action bedroom shared by children or teenagers. The room is bright and tidy, with bunk beds, shelves, sports gear, posters, and a dartboard on the wall. Three young people are gathered around handheld games: a girl sits cross-legged on the floor in front, holding a small device and concentrating on it, while two blond boys in matching light grey tracksuits with dark stripes and green shirts sit on the lower bunk behind her, leaning forward to watch. They appear excited and engaged, their attention fixed on the games.\n\nA white Nintendo Game & Watch multi-screen handheld is shown open in someone’s hands. It has two small grey LCD screens, one above the other, with game graphics on both screens. The device is hinged like a tiny book, with control buttons on the lower right and left. Tiny black character shapes and ladders or platforms are visible on the screens, suggesting a game spread across both displays. The player’s thumbs rest near t